== KEY TAKEAWAYS

1. _Tearing is common_—most first-time mothers experience some degree of tear, and most are minor.

2. _Prevention is possible_ through perineal massage, warm compresses, slow crowning, and birth positioning.

3. _Routine episiotomy is outdated_—natural tears heal better than surgical cuts.

4. _Healing takes time_ but is completely manageable with ice, sitz baths, pain relief, and patience.

5. _Severe tears require extra care_ but full recovery is absolutely possible.

6. _Call your provider_ if you see signs of infection, wound problems, or symptoms that worry you.

You may not have complete control over whether you tear, but you have more influence than you might think. Talk to your provider about perineal support, advocate for slow crowning, and know that whatever happens, your body knows how to heal.

